Program: Discovery
Title: Space and the search for infrared
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwjz
Last Broadcast Date: 27 November 1995
The launch of a European rocket from French Guiana. The rocket took a satellite that can detect infrared light, but why go into space to study them? Also in the programme, detecting the heat of creation; first clear evidence of what appears to be a planet orbiting a sun-like star; and a mammoth hunt. Show less